Now Rob comes into the room and introduces himself to you. He is a doctor and \
wants to examine you. You let him. John waits outside the door during the \
examination. When you have finished the examination, John shows you around.

You find yourself in a headquarters, but John is not allowed to tell you what \
she is doing there. He assures you, however, that it is not criminal activity. \
Since he has saved you and seems nice, you don't question it further. During \
your tour, you see a small part of the headquarters: the offices, the infirmaries, \
the canteen, the shelters, and the courtyard. In the courtyard, you meet Josie. \
John introduces the two of you. She is a little younger than you but makes a \
warm impression. The two of you hit it off right away.

