At dinner, you sit with Josie, John, and Rob. You ask them how they found you \
and if they know what happened to you. John tells you that they found you by a \
river when they were out, and they have no idea how you got there or what \
happened to you. Rob takes over and tells you that your health was critical \
when John arrived with you at headquarters. Rob did everything he could to \
operate on you and treat your internal bleeding, which almost killed you and \
caused you to fall into a coma during the operation.

You didn't expect that. Josie turns to you and says that they are all glad that \
you have finally woken up. John then asks you if you would like to stay with \
them for a while, because then you would have a place to stay and you could \
certainly make yourself useful. You don't disagree, but you still say that you \
would like to think about it.

After dinner, Josie shows you your room. Your room consists of a bed, a desk \
with a PC on it, a wardrobe, and a small bathroom with a shower. Josie tells \
you to make yourself at home and that if you have any questions, you are \
welcome to ask her. You smile. She wishes you a good night and leaves.

