You lie awake in bed and sort out your thoughts. You probably won't get your \
memories back that easily, because they have to be triggered. You also know \
that it may happen that you will never remember anything again. But no matter \
what, your options now are limited. You have nowhere else to go, and everything \
just seems strange to you.

So you are willing to accept John's offer and stay here for now. You feel \
comfortable with and like the people you have met today. Your gut feeling tells \
you that they are good people who mean you no harm. In fact, you are already \
curious to see how you can make yourself useful here and what there will be to \
discover because now you have to get to know the world anew, and with this \
thought, you go to sleep.

