It is a rainy and calm day. You also happen to not have any open tasks for work. \
So, you decide to go back to the library. There, you wander through the aisles \
and smile at some of the sections: video games, cooking, etc. 

Then you pass a section called Yearbooks. Curious about what you might find \
there, you enter the aisle. The various bookshelves contain many books that \
look alike. These are yearbooks from various universities. A bookshelf that \
contains blue and white yearbooks catches your attention.

You take out one of the newer yearbooks and flip through it. There are only \
pictures of graduates and special awards for them. You close the book and put \
it back. You take out a much older yearbook and flip through it. As you flip \
through it, you come across a face that looks very familiar. The name under \
this picture is Henry Reese. So this is your father. In the picture, your \
father is smiling, and with his horn-rimmed glasses, he looks like a typical \
nerd. 

You sit down on the floor and start dreaming. You keep looking at the pictures \
and smiling as you relive some childhood memories.

