You are lucky the college is only hours away, yet you have to leave early in the \
morning to be back at headquarters by evening. Food has been prepared for the \
trip and loaded into the car. A few extra men will accompany you. You borrowed \
a book from Josie to make the drive pass quickly. 

After the hour-long drive, you finally arrive at the university. The campus \
seems quite large, yet it is relatively empty. You suppose that it must be \
semester break. 

You look for the building of the faculty to which your father belonged. Since \
he studied computer science, it is probably the building of the computer \
science faculty. The campus is well-marked, so you should have no trouble \
finding it. As you stand in front of it, you notice that it is a relatively \
modern building. You enter it and come to a foyer. There are some awards \
hanging on the walls in the foyer. You walk over to them to take a closer look. \
Amazed, you notice that some of these awards have your name on them. They are \
all awards for outstanding achievements in hackathons. One award even has your \
father's name on it, also because of a hackathon.

