In the middle of the night, you reach the headquarters. After unloading the car \
and having something to eat, everyone goes to sleep. 

The next day, you wake up late in the afternoon. Since you don't have any \
assignments, you spend the whole afternoon researching a little about yourself \
on the Internet. However, you can't find anything you didn't already know, and \
the research took so long that it is now already time for dinner.

When you get to the cafeteria, Josie, John, and Rob are standing around a table. \
Rob is presenting his latest school physics experiment: a chocolate marshmallow \
in a vacuum. You join them just as Rob is about to show everyone his experiment. \
The chocolate marshmallow is in a glass container, and there is a hose \
connected to it. Rob closes the valve on the hose and tells everyone to pay \
close attention. 

A vacuum is created in the glass container, which causes the chocolate \
marshmallow to inflate. Everyone is now staring at Rob. Now Rob opens the valve \
on the hose again, and the chocolate marshmallow contracts again because air is \
now getting into the glass container. You think to yourself that this is not \
very exciting, but in order not to seem rude, you smile. During dinner, the \
others explain to Rob that they had this experiment in school and that it is \
therefore no longer exciting. Rob doesn't let this take away his joy.

