When you decrypt the file, a directory opens that contains a lot of files. So \
you scroll through the directory and discover a tall, powerfully built man on a \
thumbnail of a png file. You open the image and you black out.

You are sitting in a café when a man approaches you. He skates your hand and \
introduces himself as Mr. Aaron Grayson. He asks you if he can sit down for a \
moment and you politely gesture to the chair across from you. He tells you that \
he owns a software company and that he heard about your algorithm.

After the small conversation with Mr. Grayson he hands you his business card \
and you assure him that you will listen to his offer.

Now you are sitting in a rented office in a high-rise building. You are \
suspicious of the situation. After a friendly greeting, he leads you into a \
conference room where his lawyer is already sitting. After you sit down across \
from the lawyer and Mr. Grayson, the lawyer slides you the contract with the \
offer. You open the contract and read it over. The offer states that you will \
receive 5.5 million euros and that you must sign a non-disclosure agreement and \
assign all patent rights. When you have finished reading the contract, you \
close it. On the first page of the contract, is the name of the company: Aaron \
Grayson Technologies...AGT.

You feel uneasy, so you ask Mr. Grayson to tell you what your algorithm will be \
used for and that you will need a proof of that. Mr. Grayson tells you that \
this is not possible because it is a company secret. You notice how his facial \
expressions and gestures change, which confirms that something suspicious is \
going on. Suddenly, he doesn't seem so friendly. You tell him that you are also \
willing to sign a confidentiality agreement, especially since you would know a \
company secret anyway because it is your algorithm. You make it clear that this \
is non-negotiable. 

He starts nervously grinding his teeth, and tells you that he plans on using \
your algorithm to send software components more easily, since your compression \
algorithm would make the size of the files much smaller. You realize that he is \
trying to disguise his true intention, since it would theoretically also be \
possible to compress and send malicious malware, and you fear that this is \
exactly his plan.

You think about of the blog posts you wrote on the Darknet to see if anyone has \
information about the company. You had made a comment under a different \
account, containing a file with all the information you could find about AGT \
and Mr. Grayson. This is your insurance in case something should happen to you.

You come across very determined to Mr. Grayson "I am sorry Mr. Grayson, but we \
will never be able to come to any agreement. I have seen through your intentions \
and cannot ethically represent them." You get up and go to the door. As you are \
at the door you hear something bang, and he yells, "You will regret this, I \
will make sure of it myself if you leave now." You stare into his eyes and say, \
"The main thing is that my algorithm will never get in your hands" and leave.

