secret exit and they need to stay calm. Next, John pulls a hat out of his \
pocket. He walks out of the alley and turns right. There is a cross street off \
to the right. When John returns, he winks at you as he tells you that false \
tracks can never be a bad thing.

Now a light flashes on John's wristband. He is about to explain to you what it \
means when you hear a bang. Your pursuers have blown open the door through \
which you had just escaped. You take cover, but in such a way that you can \
still see your pursuers. You are looking around when one of them disappears in \
the direction John had just gone. The pursuer, who has disappeared from sight, \
calls out to the others that he has found a cap and that it is still warm, which \
means that the fugitives have fled in that direction. Thereupon, the other \
pursuers also run in that direction.

John presses the button on his wristband, and an engine noise is heard. Then \
you see the car pull up at the beginning of the alley. You can now simply \
vanish unnoticed.

